---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import fsharpLogo from "../images/fsharp-logo.svg";
import David from "../images/authors/DavidSchaefer.jpg";
import Edgar from "../images/authors/EdgarGonzalez.jpg";
import Florian from "../images/authors/FlorianVerdonck.jpg";
import Ronald from "../images/authors/RonaldSchlenker.jpg";
import { StaticRedirectNotAvailable } from "astro/dist/core/errors/errors-data";
---

<Layout title="Hire professional OSS contributors">
  <main>
    <header>
      <div class="container">
        <h1>Hiring the right people can move the needle in OSS</h1>
      </div>
    </header>
    <style>
      header {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--white);
        padding: var(--spacing-600) var(--spacing-300);
        background: var(--key-950);
        color: var(--yellow-300);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--yellow-400);

        h1 {
          font-size: var(--font-700);
          text-transform: uppercase;
          margin: 0;
        }
      }

      @media screen and (min-width: 768px) {
        header {
          padding: var(--spacing-950) 0;

          h1 {
            font-size: var(--font-900);
          }
        }
      }
    </style>
    <section id="lead">
      <div class="container">
        <p>
          Over the years, the core members of <strong class="key"
            >Amplifying F#</strong
          > have been at the forefront of many <strong class="cyan"
            >open-source adventures</strong
          >.<br />
           These men are known for their numerous contributions, expertise and
          <strong class="yellow">dedication to F#</strong>.<br />
        </p>
        <p>
          Today, some of these individuals can be hired for <strong
            class="magenta">contracting work</strong
          >.<br />
           If you have a problem, if no one else can help, and if you can find
          them...
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <style>
      #lead {
        background: var(--key-950);
        color: var(--white);
        font-size: var(--font-500);
        padding: var(--spacing-600) var(--spacing-300);

        p:first-child {
          margin-top: 0;
        }

        strong {
          font-weight: 200;
          font-size: var(--font-600);
        }

        .cyan {
          color: var(--cyan-500);
          text-shadow: var(--cyan-400) 2px 0 10px;
        }

        .magenta {
          color: var(--magenta-300);
          text-shadow: var(--magenta-400) 2px 0 10px;
        }

        .yellow {
          color: var(--yellow-400);
          text-shadow: var(--yellow-400) 2px 0 10px;
        }
      }

      @media screen and (min-width: 768px) {
        #lead {
          padding-block: var(--spacing-800);
        }
      }
    </style>
    <section id="why">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Why hire someone?</h2>
        <p>
          In the IT industry, we <strong>take OSS for granted</strong>. We
          typically assume it is free to use and if there is a problem, someone
          else will solve it. The downside of course is that <em
            >nobody cares if something isn't working</em
          > for you. It was free to begin with, so there is no refund and you
          should send a pull request to solve your own problem.
        </p>
        <p>
          Of course sending that <em
            >PR can require extensive know-how of the OSS project</em
          >. You might not have that particular skill set and nothing ever comes
          of it.
        </p>
        <p>
          There can be various reasons why an OSS problem remains unsolved and
          we encourage you to put the right people on it. <strong
            >We wish to normalize paying someone to do open-source work.</strong
          ><br />It really doesn't have to be us, but please open up to the
          idea.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <style>
      #why {
        background-color: var(--magenta-950);
        color: var(--cyan-50);

        h2 {
          text-align: right;
          text-transform: uppercase;
          margin-block: var(--spacing-600);
        }

        p:first-of-type {
          margin-top: 0;
        }

        p {
          margin-block: var(--spacing-500);
          font-size: var(--font-500);
        }

        strong {
          color: var(--magenta-300);
        }

        em {
          text-decoration: underline;
          text-decoration-color: var(--magenta-500);
        }
      }

      @media screen and (min-width: 768px) {
        #why {
          p {
          }
        }
      }
    </style>
    <section id="money">
      <h2>The secret ingredient is money</h2>
      <p class="container">
        Most of the <strong>successful F# open-source projects</strong> have
        thrived because
        <strong>companies invested serious money</strong> into it. Some stories
        are more publicly known than others, but know that only the sun is free.
        Money often allows <strong
          >someone to work on the project during broad day light</strong
        > and that is essential to make projects flourish.
      </p>
    </section>
    <style>
      #money {
        background-color: var(--cyan-200);
        padding-block: var(--spacing-600);

        h2 {
          text-transform: uppercase;
          text-align: center;
          color: var(--cyan-800);
          margin-top: 0;
          margin-bottom: var(--spacing-600);
          padding: 0;
          border-radius: var(--radius);
          font-size: var(--font-700);
        }

        p {
          font-size: var(--font-600);
          max-width: 80%;
          margin-inline: auto;
        }
      }

      @media screen and (min-width: 768px) {
        #money {
          padding-block: var(--spacing-800);

          h2 {
          }

          p {
            max-width: 50%;
            margin-top: 0;
          }
        }
      }
    </style>
    <section id="contractors" class="container">
      <h2>Hire Amplifying FSharp's finest</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Amplifying FSharp is no legal entity and thus cannot take any direct
        assignments. Most members have a freelance business and can be contacted
        for opportunities. We wish to inform you this is possible. Feel free to
        reach out, <em>on sait jamais</em>.
      </p>
      <div class="contractor">
        <div class="header">
          <h3 id="DavidSchaefer">David Schaefer</h3>
          <Image src={David} alt="David Schaefer" />
        </div>
        <div class="body">
          <p>
            Greetings, I'm David, aka dawe, a freelancing software engineer with a big 
            ‚ù§Ô∏è‚Äçüî• for functional programming. I have experience with a number of functional languages 
            and enjoy the diversity in this paradigm.
          </p>
          <p>
            My passion for Open Source goes back many years. 
            Currently, I'm focused on the F# ecosystem and help maintain 
            <a href="https://github.com/fsprojects/fantomas" target="_blank">various</a> 
            <a href="https://github.com/ionide/FSharp.Analyzers.SDK" target="_blank">projects</a>. 
            As part of the <a href="https://opensource.gresearch.com/" target="_blank">G-Research Open-Source team</a>, 
            I gained experience especially in developer tooling, such as the 
            <a href="https://devblogs.microsoft.com/dotnet/safer-recursion-in-fsharp/" target="_blank">compiler</a> 
            or <a href="https://github.com/fsharp/FsAutoComplete" target="_blank">IDE</a> support.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="contact">
          <a
            href="mailto:dawedawe@posteo.de?subject=Contracting%20Amplifying%20FSharp"
            target="_blank"
          >
            <Icon name="mdi-light:email" height="32" width="32" />
          </a>
          <a href="https://github.com/dawedawe" target="_blank">
            <Icon name="bi:github" height="32" width="32" />
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/david-schaefer-a44177a8/"
            target="_blank"
          >
            <Icon name="bi:linkedin" height="32" width="32" />
          </a>
          <a href="https://www.function-type.com/" target="_blank">
            <Icon name="ph:globe-light" height="32" width="32" />
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="contractor">
        <div class="header">
          <h3 id="EdgarGonzalez">Edgar Gonzalez</h3>
          <Image src={Edgar} alt="Edgar Gonzalez" />
        </div>
        <div class="body">
          <p>
            I'm Edgar Gonzalez, a software developer focused on F#, .NET, Swift, with passion for functional programming and open source.
            I'm a member of the AmplifyingF# initiative where i tried to help the F# community to grow and be more inclusive.</p>
          <p>
          <p>I'm a regular contributor to <strong>F# open-source projects</strong> like
            <a href=" https://github.com/dotnet/fsharp/pulls?q=is%3Apr+author%3Aedgarfgp" target="_blank">F# Compiler</a> and
            <a href="(https://github.com/fabulous-dev)" target="_blank">Fabulous</a>.
            Thanks to my contributions to the F# compiler, I was showcased as <a href="https://devblogs.microsoft.com/dotnet/announcing-fsharp-7/#community-contributor" target="_blank">Community Contributor</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            My experience with C# F#, Swift and functional programming has allowed to develop high performant and reliable mobile apps for iOS and Android using UIKit, SwiftUI and .NET.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="contact">
          <a
            href="mailto:edgar@mail.to?subject=Contracting%20Amplifying%20FSharp"
            target="_blank"
          >
            <Icon name="mdi-light:email" height="32" width="32" />
          </a>
          <a href="https://github.com/edgarfgp" target="_blank">
            <Icon name="bi:github" height="32" width="32" />
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/edgargonzalezdev/"
            target="_blank"
          >
            <Icon name="bi:linkedin" height="32" width="32" />
          </a>
          <a href="https://devconflicts.com/" target="_blank">
            <Icon name="ph:globe-light" height="32" width="32" />
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="contractor nojaf">
        <div class="header">
          <h3 id="FlorianVerdonck">Florian Verdonck</h3>
          <Image src={Florian} alt="Florian Verdonck" />
        </div>
        <div class="body">
          <p>
            Hi there, I'm Florian, also known as <strong>nojaf</strong> on
            GitHub! I've had the privilege of contributing to pivotal <strong
              >F# open-source projects</strong
            > over the years. This includes working on the F#
            <strong>compiler and developing essential tooling</strong>.
          </p>
          <p>
            One of my earliest successes was rejuvenating the <a
              href="https://fsprojects.github.io/fantomas/"
              target="_blank">Fantomas project</a
            >, which taught me invaluable lessons in nurturing an open-source
            project. This experience enhanced not only my technical expertise
            but also my ability to navigate the open-source community
            effectively.
          </p>
          <p>
            I've also had the amazing opportunity to collaborate with the
            <a href="https://opensource.gresearch.com/" target="_blank"
              >G-Research Open-Source team</a
            >. There, I made significant contributions to the F# components of
            the dotnet SDK. At one point, I was even recognized as the Featured
            <a
              href="https://devblogs.microsoft.com/dotnet/announcing-dotnet-8-rc2/#community-contributor"
              >Community Contributor</a
            >.
          </p>
          <p>
            In addition to this, I have a strong interest in web development. I
            apply my front-end skills to create tools like the <a
              href="https://fsprojects.github.io/fantomas-tools"
              target="_blank">Fantomas online tools</a
            > and contribute to the <a
              href="https://github.com/fsprojects/FSharp.Formatting/issues/849"
              target="_blank">modern theme for F# Formatting</a
            >.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="contact">
          <a
            href="mailto:florian@nojaf.com?subject=Contracting%20Amplifying%20FSharp"
            target="_blank"
          >
            <Icon name="mdi-light:email" height="32" width="32" />
          </a>
          <a href="https://github.com/nojaf" target="_blank">
            <Icon name="bi:github" height="32" width="32" />
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/florian-verdonck/"
            target="_blank"
          >
            <Icon name="bi:linkedin" height="32" width="32" />
          </a>
          <a href="https://blog.nojaf.com/about" target="_blank">
            <Icon name="ph:globe-light" height="32" width="32" />
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="contractor">
        <div class="header">
          <h3 id="RonaldSchlenker">Ronald Schlenker</h3>
          <Image src={Ronald} alt="Ronald Schlenker" />
        </div>
        <div class="body">
          <p>
            Ronald is a Frankfurt/Germany based programmer and software developer with more than 20 years of experience. As an expert in F#, C# .Net as well as in the web environment since day one, he supports his clients in the design and implementation of complex business applications and technically highly sophisticated libraries and frameworks. He is an active and recognized member of the F# community. In addition to his day-to-day work for clients, Ronald consults and coaches teams in progressive fields such as functional software development, and he is involved in many successful open source projects.
          </p>
          <p>
            When developing software systems, mastering complexity - i.e. dividing an unmanageable overall system into individual, comprehensible artifacts with clear dependencies - is one of the greatest challenges of all. For this to succeed, technical skills are just as important as a willingness to communicate, teamwork, the ability to engage in constructive discourse and the recognition of problems and their solutions.
          </p>
          <p>
            I see programming languages as tools that enable the developer to formulate problems with exactly the right degree of expressiveness to achieve maximum comprehensibility. It is therefore necessary to know which language tools exist and, above all, how they can be used sensibly in the respective context. The same applies to principles: It is good to know them. The big challenge is to understand what they mean for everyday programming and how you can incorporate them into your work in a meaningful way.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="contact">
          <a
            href="mailto:schlenkr@screen9.de?subject=Contracting%20Amplifying%20FSharp"
            target="_blank"
          >
            <Icon name="mdi-light:email" height="32" width="32" />
          </a>
          <a href="https://github.com/schlenkR" target="_blank">
            <Icon name="bi:github" height="32" width="32" />
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ronald-s-297a675/"
            target="_blank"
          >
            <Icon name="bi:linkedin" height="32" width="32" />
          </a>
          <a href="https://www.xing.com/profile/Ronald_Schlenker" target="_blank">
            <Icon name="ph:globe-light" height="32" width="32" />
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <style>
      #contractors {
        .intro {
          max-width: 75%;
          font-style: italic;
          margin-block: var(--spacing-500);
        }

        h2 {
          font-size: var(--font-700);
        }

        .contractor {
          box-shadow: 0 1px 1px var(--shadow-color);
          background-color: var(--key-900);
          background: linear-gradient(
            180deg,
            var(--key-900) 0%,
            var(--key-950) 100%
          );
          padding: var(--spacing-400);
          color: var(--white);
          margin-bottom: var(--spacing-400);

          .header {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            justify-content: space-between;

            h3 {
              text-transform: uppercase;
              margin-top: 0;
              font-size: var(--font-600);
              margin-right: var(--spacing-100);
            }

            img {
              height: 160px;
              width: 160px;
              object-fit: cover;
            }
          }

          .body {
            margin-block: var(--spacing-500);
          }

          .contact {
            display: flex;
            gap: var(--spacing-400);
            justify-content: space-between;

            a {
              color: var(--cyan-500);
              transition: all 200ms;
            }

            a:hover {
              color: var(--cyan-200);
            }
          }

          &.nojaf {
            background: #ffe710;
            color: var(--key-950);
            @import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Mohave:wght@600&display=swap");

            .header {
              h3 {
                font-family: "Mohave", sans-serif;
                font-weight: 600;
                font-size: var(--font-700);
              }
            }

            .contact {
              a {
                color: var(--key-800);
                padding-bottom: var(--spacing-100);

                &:hover {
                  color: var(--key-950);
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }

      @media screen and (min-width: 768px) {
        #contractors {
          .intro {
            max-width: 66%;
          }

          .contractor {
            margin-bottom: var(--spacing-600);

            .header {
              display: inline;

              img {
                height: 250px;
                width: 250px;
                object-fit: cover;
                float: right;
              }
            }

            .body {
              min-height: 250px;
              width: calc(100% - 250px - var(--spacing-400));
            }

            .contact {
              justify-content: space-evenly;
              gap: 0;
            }
          }
        }
      }
    </style>
  </main>
</Layout>
<style>
  section {
    padding: var(--spacing-400);
  }
</style>
